: "2017-09-12T19:42:23.471590+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 39810070}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109/comments/47921059.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools/issues/109#comment-47921059"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 109, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}ts=python"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "release-tools", "full_name": "osrf/release-tools", "uuid": "{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}"}, "title": "Use brew bottle more and host bottles at bintray"}, "content": {"raw": "There's a useful explanation of the homebrew core workflow based on how bintray works:\n\n* https://github.com/Homebrew/homebrew-core/issues/31511#issuecomment-421810684", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>There's a useful explanation of the homebrew core workflow based on how bintray works:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Homebrew/homebrew-core/issues/31511#issuecomment-421810684\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">https://github.com/Homebrew/homebrew-core/issues/31511#issuecomment-421810684</a></li>\n</ul>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-09-21T06:20:09.202085+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 47921059}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109/comments/48009361.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools/issues/109#comment-48009361"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 109, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}ts=python"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "release-tools", "full_name": "osrf/release-tools", "uuid": "{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}"}, "title": "Use brew bottle more and host bottles at bintray"}, "content": {"raw": "I've looked into a more standard approach to updating the bottle hashes in the formula using `brew bottle --merge --write x.bottle.json` with arguments `--no-commit --keep-old`, but there is a challenge since we don't upload all our bottles to the same URL (ie. gazebosim.org/distributions/gazebo/releases and gazebosim.org/distributions/sdformat/releases differ). The challenge is that the `root_url` must already be specified in the json file, which means that the `--root_url=http://gazebosim.org/distributions/x/releases` argument must be passed to `brew test-bot` when the bottles are created. This is fine if a pull request only modifies different versions of the same formula (like `gazebo7`, `gazebo8` or `gazebo9`), but if it modifies different formula (like `ignition-msgs1`, `ignition-transport4`, and `gazebo9` in [osrf/homebrew-simulation#492](https://github.com/osrf/homebrew-simulation/pull/492)) then the root URL's won't match.\n\nWe could consider changing out hosting pattern for homebrew bottles to put them all in a single folder.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I've looked into a more standard approach to updating the bottle hashes in the formula using <code>brew bottle --merge --write x.bottle.json</code> with arguments <code>--no-commit --keep-old</code>, but there is a challenge since we don't upload all our bottles to the same URL (ie. <a href=\"http://gazebosim.org/distributions/gazebo/releases\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">gazebosim.org/distributions/gazebo/releases</a> and <a href=\"http://gazebosim.org/distributions/sdformat/releases\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">gazebosim.org/distributions/sdformat/releases</a> differ). The challenge is that the <code>root_url</code> must already be specified in the json file, which means that the <code>--root_url=http://gazebosim.org/distributions/x/releases</code> argument must be passed to <code>brew test-bot</code> when the bottles are created. This is fine if a pull request only modifies different versions of the same formula (like <code>gazebo7</code>, <code>gazebo8</code> or <code>gazebo9</code>), but if it modifies different formula (like <code>ignition-msgs1</code>, <code>ignition-transport4</code>, and <code>gazebo9</code> in <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"https://github.com/osrf/homebrew-simulation/pull/492\" rel=\"nofollow\">osrf/homebrew-simulation#492</a>) then the root URL's won't match.</p>\n<p>We could consider changing out hosting pattern for homebrew bottles to put them all in a single folder.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-09-25T23:00:06.204100+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 48009361}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109/comments/48177672.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools/issues/109#comment-48177672"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 109, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}ts=python"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "release-tools", "full_name": "osrf/release-tools", "uuid": "{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}"}, "title": "Use brew bottle more and host bottles at bintray"}, "content": {"raw": "I've been testing an approach that uses a common root_url for storing all the homebrew bottles with the following branch:\n\n* #!/osrf/release-tools/branch/brew_root_url_upload\n\nThe challenge is that the preferred way to update the bottle checksums requires all the json files to be available and passed to `brew bottle --merge --write`. We are currently processing the json files one at a time. @\\_jrivero_ I think this would require restructuring the way the jenkins jobs are set up. If it's too much work, we may have to keep doing it the old way.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>I've been testing an approach that uses a common root_url for storing all the homebrew bottles with the following branch:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#!/osrf/release-tools/branch/brew_root_url_upload\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">#!/osrf/release-tools/branch/brew_root_url_upload</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The challenge is that the preferred way to update the bottle checksums requires all the json files to be available and passed to <code>brew bottle --merge --write</code>. We are currently processing the json files one at a time. @_jrivero_ I think this would require restructuring the way the jenkins jobs are set up. If it's too much work, we may have to keep doing it the old way.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-10-04T23:38:08.803279+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 48177672}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109/comments/48289246.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools/issues/109#comment-48289246"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 109, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}ts=python"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "release-tools", "full_name": "osrf/release-tools", "uuid": "{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}"}, "title": "Use brew bottle more and host bottles at bintray"}, "content": {"raw": "we can change the different jobs by a Matrix job to have all json files in one job #!/osrf/release-tools/pull-requests/675/use-matrix-job-to-build-all-brew-bottle/diff", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>we can change the different jobs by a Matrix job to have all json files in one job <a href=\"#!/osrf/release-tools/pull-requests/675/use-matrix-job-to-build-all-brew-bottle/diff\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">#!/osrf/release-tools/pull-requests/675/use-matrix-job-to-build-all-brew-bottle/diff</a></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-10-11T12:25:12.035328+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Jose Luis Rivero", "uuid": "{d12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/109284c8b83411dbc7492138f6167e9ed=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsJR-5.png"}}, "nickname": "Jose Luis Rivero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:155a32e2-420c-4d50-98e0-0e722f63f906"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 48289246}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109/comments/48361370.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools/issues/109#comment-48361370"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 109, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}ts=python"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "release-tools", "full_name": "osrf/release-tools", "uuid": "{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}"}, "title": "Use brew bottle more and host bottles at bintray"}, "content": {"raw": "we will use `brew bottle --merge --write` in pull request #676, but I don't think we need to use bintray", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>we will use <code>brew bottle --merge --write</code> in <a href=\"#!/osrf/release-tools/pull-requests/676/use-single-root_url-for-brew-bottles-use\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">pull request #676</a>, but I don't think we need to use bintray</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-10-15T20:19:47.521826+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 48361370}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109/comments/48384640.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools/issues/109#comment-48384640"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools/issues/109.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 109, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/release-tools.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/release-tools"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}ts=python"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "release-tools", "full_name": "osrf/release-tools", "uuid": "{41811d3d-19d0-428e-a134-976595e72508}"}, "title": "Use brew bottle more and host bottles at bintray"}, "content": {"raw": "marking as complete since we now use brew bottle since pull request #676", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>marking as complete since we now use brew bottle since <a href=\"#!/osrf/release-tools/pull-requests/676/use-single-root_url-for-brew-bottles-use\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"ap-connect-link\">pull request #676</a></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-10-16T19:29:43.113292+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 48384640}], "page": 1, "size": 10}